@node "History" "History"
@next "Author"
@prev "Distribution"


  @{b}2.0:@{ub} First release.

  @{b}3.0:@{ub} Fixed FAST RAM bug (crash on Amigas with FAST RAM)

  @{b}3.1:@{ub} Added logging to file.
       Added menus.

  @{b}3.2:@{ub} Now window open on Public screen.
       Argument string added.
       Quit Save bug fixed (If you Quit from program it don't save).
       Settings menu added.
       Added some program settings.
       Menu bug fixed.
       Some other small bugs fixed.
       Added ARexx support (You can control program via ARexx)
                           (Start and Stop time via ARexx scripts)
                           (Demo scripts included)
       Added ARexx script for logfile processing.
                           (Thanks to Feril).
@endnode

@node "Cli" "Cli    "


   You can run NetTime from scripts and AmigaDos.

   NetTime X/N,Y/N,CXP/N,MINT/N,LOG/S,AREXX/S,PATH/K.

           X.Y   - NetTime window coordinates.
           CXP   - Commodities priority.
           MINT  - Minimal logging time. (If on-line time smaller
                   that MINT, call not logged.)
           LOG   - Enable/Disable logging.
           AREXX - Control method - ARexx/Modem.
                   If AREXX flag is set then NetTime is controled
                   via ARexx port (see @{"ARexx" link "ARexx" 0}),if not then via
                   modem (only for standart Amiga serial port).
           PATH  - Path of logfile output dir,default PROGDIR:.

   If you run NetTime from Cli, then Settings menu is Disabled.
   You can use only Project menu.
@endnode

@node "Workbench" "Workbench         "


  For start NetTime program from WB, simple click on Icon, or put
  program into WBStartup drawer.

  @{b}Menus:@{ub}

       Project

             Logging  - You can Enable/Disable logging.
             About    - About program.
             Quit     - Exit.

       Settings

             Change   - Change program Prefs.

  @{b}Program Window:@{ub}

       In program window you can see current or last call time.
       If anim is move then modem is on-line and otherwise.

  @{b}Prefs:@{ub}

       X,Y     - Program window coordinates.
       Grab    - Press this button for grab current window position.
       Log     - Logging status.
       Ct      - Control type Modem/ARexx (see also @{"ARexx" link "ARexx" 0}).
       CX Pri  - Commodities priority.
       MinTime - Minimal logging time.(If on-line time smaller that
                 MinTime call not logged.)
       Path    - Logfile path (Drawer name with full path).
       S       - Select logfile drawer.

       Save    - Save settings.
       Cancel  - Exit without save.

    Note: Maked changes only take effect on next program run.
@endnode

@node "ARexx" "ARexx             "


  You can control NetTime via ARexx port:

    Port name:  NETTIME

    Supported commands: START,STOP,QUIT.

    Commands START and STOP only work if you select ARexx control type
    from prefs.

    START - start timer.
    STOP  - stop timer.

    QUIT  - Exit from NetTime.

    Examples ARexx scripts is included into archive.
@endnode

@node "Calc" "Calc ARexx Script "


  This ARexx script is written and developed by Feril.

  You can use this script for logfile processing.You get information
  about numbers of calls,crashes,time costs and other.

  ******************** WARNING ***********************

  Before using that script you MUST make some changes
  into it.More information you can find into it.

  ****************************************************

  For script start simple click on Calc.rexx Icon. All results is
  stored to file called log_even.
@endnode

